  "id": "01942b60-803f-714e-95f9-f357a7cfbe36",
  "templateTitle": "Keep Deployment's pods down",
  "templateDescription": "Check what happens when all pods of a Kubernetes deployment aren't coming up again. \n## Motivation\nTypically, Kubernetes tries to keep as many pods running as desired for a Kubernetes deployment. However, some circumstances may prevent Kubernetes from achieving this, like missing resources in the cluster, problems with the deployment's probes, or a CrashLoopBackOff.\nYou should validate what happens to your overall provided service when a given deployment is directly affected by this or one of the upstream services used by your deployment.\n\n## Structure\nTo keep the pods down for a given deployment, we first kill all the pods in the deployment. Simultaneously, we will scale down the Kubernetes deployment to 0 to simulate that these pods can't be scheduled again.\nAt the of the experiment, we automatically roll back the deployment's scale to the initial value.",
  "placeholders": [
    {
      "key": "k8sClusterName",
      "name": "Kubernetes Cluster Name",
      "description": "### What is the Kubernetes cluster of the deployment?"
    },
    {
      "key": "k8sNamespace",
      "name": "Kubernetes Namespace",
      "description": "### What is the Kubernetes namespace of the deployment?"
    },
    {
      "key": "k8sDeployment",
      "name": "Kubernetes Deployment",
      "description": "### What is the name of the Kubernetes deployment whose pods you want to keep down?"
    },
    {
      "key": "k8sPodDownDuration",
      "name": "Duration Pods Down",
      "description": "### How long should we keep the pods down?Specify how long you want to keep the pods down, e.g., 3 minutes."
    }
  ],
  "tags": [
    "Deployment",
    "Upstream Service",
    "Kubernetes"
  ],
  "experimentName": "Keep pods down of deployment [[k8sDeployment]]",
  "hypothesis": "Validate what happens when pods aren't coming up for a given time, e.g., 3 minutes. Validate what happens to the given deployment as well as downstream service depending on the unavailable service as upstream.",
